IX-B. BJORN — THE DRAGON-BORN AWAKENING (the long fuse, paced across adventures)
  Bjorn was ALWAYS the Dragonborn (the name is the buried clue: dragon-BORN).
  The awakening is a slow, multi-adventure progression, never a single beat:
   1. THE SPEED (this journey): the War-Hound's velocity wakes to save Mila
      from the two dragons (Section III). Involuntary, terrifying to him,
      witnessed but unnamed. The dragon-soul stirs.
   2. THE WORD (a later sighting): he can learn his FIRST shout only after he
      SEES a dragon Word Wall — he is SELF-TAUGHT, because the Greybeards
      cannot sense what he is and will never summon or train him (no one can
      detect a Dragonborn). The wild Dragonborn, learning from walls the
      institution is blind to. Unlike the videogame he learns ALL THREE words
      of a shout at once (so it does not drag out). He will NOT use it for a
      long while — he is resisting his own nature.
   3. THE RETURN (endgame): grief (Kyboh) + need (the party) + the child
      (Mila) thaw the renunciation. He picks the power back up not for the
      world but for his people. Skuldafn -> Sovngarde -> Alduin is where the
      old Kyboh/Shor lore migrates (the Draconic Genesis treatise is the
      framework for what is happening to him).
  [GM TBD: WHERE the first Word Wall sighting happens — Bleak Falls Barrow
